description: Borrowed from Greek μουσακάς (mousakás), from Turkish musakka, from Arabic مُسَقَّعَة‎ (musaqqaʕa) or originally from Arabic مُصَقَّعَة‎ (muṣaqqaʕa), from the trilateral root ص ق ع‎ (ṣ-q-ʕ): “to hit, to pound, to smash”.

entries.meaning: A dish consisting of layers of minced lamb or beef, sliced aubergine (eggplant) or potatoes, tomatoes and béchamel sauce, baked in the oven.
